{
  "article_id": "Warner1894",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "In a paper by ",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. C. F. Holder",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ],
        "entity_key": "cho",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "printed in ",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "THE HERALD",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ],
        "entity_key": "laherald",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "of November 30th, mention is made of a theory regarding ",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the islands lying off the coast and to the south",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "of ",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Point Concepcion",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_pc",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", to the effect that ",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the islands",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "are vestiges of a sunken continent that was inhabited by a race of people other than found upon the American continent at the time of its discovery by Europeans.",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "In support of this theory it is stated by ",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the writer",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ],
        "entity_key": "cho",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "that ",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Dr. Carr",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ],
        "entity_key": "carr",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "found human skulls upon the island of ",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Catalina",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_scatalina",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "differing so far from the skulls of people now inhabiting the earth as to warrant a belief that they were the skulls of an entirely different and extinct race.",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "It may be pertinent to enquire of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. Holder",
        "entity_key": "cho",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "what length of time human skulls would retain their form and structure if exposed on the surface or buried in the ground, under climatic conditions like those of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Catalina",
        "entity_key": "i_scatalina",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Another circumstance referred to by "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. Holder",
        "entity_key": "cho",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "in support of the theory is that "
      },
      {
        "text": "a woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "brought from the island of "
      },
      {
        "text": "St. Nicholas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "could not speak any one of the dialects spoken by the Indians along the shore of California."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "At the time of the founding of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "missions of Upper California",
        "entity_key": "mi_mainlandmissions",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", the islands of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Rosa",
        "entity_key": "i_sr",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Cruz",
        "entity_key": "i_scruz",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Catalina",
        "entity_key": "i_scatalina",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "were all inhabited by "
      },
      {
        "text": "Indians",
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", brought over to the "
      },
      {
        "text": "mainland",
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and incorporated into the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Indian communities of the missions",
        "entity_key": "natam_missionindians",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Intercourse had previously been kept up between the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Indians living on the islands",
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "and "
      },
      {
        "text": "those on the mainland",
        "entity_key": "natam_missionindians",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and from their proximity to the "
      },
      {
        "text": "mainland",
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", the "
      },
      {
        "text": "mission fathers",
        "entity_key": "misfats",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "had no difficulty in gathering them into the fold of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Roman Catholic church",
        "entity_key": "ch_catholic",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". The distance to "
      },
      {
        "text": "St. Nicholas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "however, was so great that "
      },
      {
        "text": "the fathers",
        "entity_key": "misfats",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "and the soldiers, who guarded them, had no intercourse with the "
      },
      {
        "text": "inland [island] tribes",
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "In 1832 there were, and had been for many years, "
      },
      {
        "text": "two Indian villages",
        "entity_keys": [
          "village1",
          "village2"
        ],
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "in the town of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Los Angeles",
        "entity_key": "ci_la",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "; one was "
      },
      {
        "text": "near the intersection of Aliso and Alameda streets",
        "entity_key": "village1",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", the people of which were of and they spoke the same dialect as the "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Gabriel Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". The other village was "
      },
      {
        "text": "near where the crossing of Eighth and San Pedro streets now is",
        "entity_key": "village2",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". These people, or their ancestors, had come from "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Catalina",
        "entity_key": "i_scatalina",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and their dialect differed slightly from that of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the other village",
        "entity_key": "village1",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "There were in "
      },
      {
        "text": "this latter village",
        "entity_key": "village2",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "some elderly men who were stonecutters. These men occasionally visited "
      },
      {
        "text": "their \"fatherland,\"",
        "entity_key": "i_scatalina",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and occupied themselves with making pots and other cooking utensils from soapstone found on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_scatalina",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". The utensils they disposed of at the missions and to the inhabitants of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the town",
        "entity_key": "ci_la",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". It was known to the people of California that in 1818, or about that time, "
      },
      {
        "text": "a vessel",
        "entity_key": "sh_ilmena",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "belonging to the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Russian-American Fur company",
        "entity_key": "rfurcompany",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", engaged in hunting sea fur-bearing animals, with "
      },
      {
        "text": "a crew of Kodiac Indian hunters",
        "entity_keys": [
          "1814huntingparty",
          "rfurcompany",
          "iba",
          "natam_aleuts",
          "natam_kodiak"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", visited the "
      },
      {
        "text": "island of St. Nicholas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and while there a dispute arose between "
      },
      {
        "text": "the other [otter] hunters",
        "entity_keys": [
          "1814huntingparty",
          "rfurcompany",
          "iba",
          "natam_aleuts",
          "natam_kodiak"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and "
      },
      {
        "text": "the natives",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". During a battle that followed nearly all "
      },
      {
        "text": "the natives",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "were killed. It was known in the early part of the fourth decade of this century to a few men who were engaged in hunting sea otter around "
      },
      {
        "text": "the islands lying off this coast",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "that there were "
      },
      {
        "text": "native inhabitants living on the island of St. Nicholas",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "In 1836 "
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain James Johnson",
        "entity_key": "jsjo",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Isaac Williams",
        "entity_key": "iwi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", both residents of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Los Angeles",
        "entity_key": "ci_la",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", sent "
      },
      {
        "text": "a boat",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "to "
      },
      {
        "text": "that island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "to bring "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Los Angeles",
        "entity_key": "ci_la",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Only seven people were found, and comprised "
      },
      {
        "text": "an elderly man and woman, a man and woman about 40 years of age respectively, one girl of about 18 years and two boys of 14 or 15 years each",
        "entity_keys": [
          "bhagroup",
          "lw",
          "bha"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". While "
      },
      {
        "text": "the boat's crew",
        "entity_keys": [
          "1835crew",
          "chu",
          "isp",
          "iwi",
          "jsjo",
          "jdy",
          "lbu",
          "natam_hawaiian",
          "nativeamericans"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "were busy with other matters "
      },
      {
        "text": "the old woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "escaped. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The remaining six",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "were taken to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Los Angeles",
        "entity_key": "ci_la",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and taken into the families of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Johnson",
        "entity_key": "jsjo",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. Williams",
        "entity_key": "iwi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "as servants, and were treated in the same manner as other Indian servants. They did not speak the same dialect of any of the Indians of the mainland with the exception of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the girl",
        "entity_keys": [
          "Nicolenowoman8",
          "halfbreeds"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who was a halfbreed; "
      },
      {
        "text": "the others",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "were all Indians and not distinguishable from the native Indian of California."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Whether from a radical change in their diet or from some other cause, ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the islanders that were brought to Los Angeles",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "soon fell sick and it was not long before all of them were dead, except ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the old man",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "bha",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who recovered with the loss of his sight.",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "He found his way to "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Pedro",
        "entity_key": "ci_sp",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", where he lived a number of years, spending most of his time along the beach gathering such shellfish for food as he could find on the rocks at low tide."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Some years later "
      },
      {
        "text": "George Neidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who devoted much of his time to hunting sea otter, was at the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Island of St. Nicholas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and brought from thence to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "that had been left by "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Johnson and Williams party",
        "entity_keys": [
          "jsjo",
          "iwi"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "She was very old and owing to her lonely life had lost the power of speech.",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "There was nothing in her physical appearance to distinguish her from the Indian race on this coast."
      }
    ]
  ]
}